Package: EnsDb.Hsapiens.v116
Title: Ensembl Based Annotation Package for Homo sapiens, Release 116
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Brian", "Lamere", email = "you@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Exposes an EnsDb object built from Ensembl release 116
    (GRCh38, June 2026) gene annotations for Homo sapiens. This is an
    independently built, unofficial package, modeled directly on the
    Bioconductor 'EnsDb.Hsapiens.vNN' package series (e.g.
    EnsDb.Hsapiens.v86, maintained via AnnotationHub/ensembldb by the
    Bioconductor project, last released for Ensembl 86). Those packages
    have not been updated to track current Ensembl releases, so this
    package fills the same role for release 116. The underlying SQLite
    database is built directly from the Ensembl GTF for release 116 using
    the 'ensembldb' package; see inst/scripts/build_ensdb.R for the full,
    reproducible build procedure, including the exact source URL and
    checksum verification. The built database is stored in this package
    as checksummed, chunked parts (to stay under GitHub's 100MB per-file
    limit) and is reassembled automatically during installation via the
    bundled 'configure' script, so the database is fully present and
    ready to use as soon as installation completes, with no separate
    manual step and no network access required at install or load time.
License: Artistic-2.0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
NeedsCompilation: no
biocViews: AnnotationData, OrganismData, Homo_sapiens
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0), ensembldb (>= 2.0.0)
